          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/tomdejong.xml" title="Tom de Jong" addr="tomdejong" type="local">Tom de Jong</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/martinescardo.xml" title="Martín Hötzel Escardó" addr="martinescardo" type="local">Martín Hötzel Escardó</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
              </fr:author>
            </fr:authors>
            <fr:date>
              <fr:year>2023</fr:year>
              <fr:month>2</fr:month>
              <fr:day>16</fr:day>
            </fr:date>
            <fr:addr>jms-002A</fr:addr>
            <fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-002A.xml</fr:route>
            <fr:title text="positively generated pointed dcpos are free">positively generated pointed dcpos are free</fr:title>
            <fr:taxon>Lemma</fr:taxon>
          </fr:frontmatter>
          <fr:mainmatter><html:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> be a <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0023.xml" title="positively generated dcpos" addr="jms-0023" type="local">positively generated</fr:link> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-001S.xml" title="pointed dcpo" addr="jms-001S" type="local">pointed</fr:link> dcpo; then <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is canonically <html:em>free</html:em> on its <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-001P.xml" title="the subdcpo spanned by positive elements" addr="jms-001P" type="local">subdcpo of positive elements</fr:link> <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A^+]]></fr:tex>. More specifically, the embedding-projection pair <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+};\alpha _A\right )\mathclose {}}\dashv {A}\xrightarrow {{\mathsf {purify}_A}}{\mathsf {L}{A^+}}]]></fr:tex> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0020.xml" title="pointed dcpos with open positivity predicates are almost free" addr="jms-0020" type="local">given by</fr:link> the <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0021.xml" title="the “purification” map" addr="jms-0021" type="local">purification map</fr:link> is an isomorphism of dcpos.</html:p>
 
   
   <fr:tree show-metadata="false" toc="false"><fr:frontmatter><fr:authors><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/tomdejong.xml" title="Tom de Jong" addr="tomdejong" type="local">Tom de Jong</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/martinescardo.xml" title="Martín Hötzel Escardó" addr="martinescardo" type="local">Martín Hötzel Escardó</fr:link></fr:author><fr:author><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:date><fr:year>2023</fr:year><fr:month>2</fr:month><fr:day>16</fr:day></fr:date><fr:addr>jms-002A/0</fr:addr><fr:route>https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-002A/0.xml</fr:route><fr:title text="positively generated pointed dcpos are free › forest://jonmsterling/jms-002A/0"><fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-002A.xml" title="positively generated pointed dcpos are free" addr="jms-002A" type="local">positively generated pointed dcpos are free</fr:link> › jms-002A/0</fr:title><fr:taxon>Proof</fr:taxon></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter>
  <html:p>First, we recall that the embedding-projection pair <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+};\alpha _A\right )\mathclose {}}\dashv \mathsf {purify}_A]]></fr:tex> <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0020.xml" title="pointed dcpos with open positivity predicates are almost free" addr="jms-0020" type="local">exists</fr:link> because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> has an <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0022.xml" title="open positivity predicate" addr="jms-0022" type="local">open positivity predicate</fr:link> by <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0027.xml" title="positively generated dcpos have open positivity predicates" addr="jms-0027" type="local">virtue of</fr:link> its <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0023.xml" title="positively generated dcpos" addr="jms-0023" type="local">positive generation</fr:link>. Therefore, the statement of this lemma is well-formed.</html:p>

  <html:p>Because <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+};\alpha _A\right )\mathclose {}}\dashv \mathsf {purify}_A]]></fr:tex> is an embedding-projection pair, it remains only to check that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathsf {purify}_A;\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+};\alpha _A]]></fr:tex> is an <html:em>inflation</html:em>, i.e. for all <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a:A]]></fr:tex> we must have <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[a \sqsubseteq  \alpha _A{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {L}{\iota ^+}{\mathopen {}\left (\mathsf {purify}_Aa\right )\mathclose {}}\right )\mathclose {}}]]></fr:tex>. As the latter is equal to <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\bigsqcup _{p:\mathsf {pos}\,a}a]]></fr:tex>, the inflation condition follows from our assumption that <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[A]]></fr:tex> is <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-0023.xml" title="positively generated dcpos" addr="jms-0023" type="local">positively generated</fr:link>.</html:p>
</fr:mainmatter></fr:tree>
 
</fr:mainmatter>
        </fr:tree>
        <fr:tree show-metadata="true" expanded="false" toc="false" numbered="false">
          <fr:frontmatter>
            <fr:authors>
              <fr:author>
                <fr:link href="https://www.jonmsterling.com/jonmsterling.xml" title="Jon Sterling" addr="jonmsterling" type="local">Jon Sterling</fr:link>
